      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPICY THANG (3) had plenty of support first-up when jumping favourite over this track and trip 13 days ago. She never got into the race after being too far back there, but she can take closer order from a better draw this time. Parnham replaces the apprentice and she can go one better. WILUNA LASS (5) led them up on resumption and couldn't hold off the winner late in the race at Belmont. It showed she was back in good order though and with the added fitness under her belt, she can go one better this time around. KINGS COURT (1) dipped second-up after a strong performance from the front fresh at Belmont. Suspect he'll try to lead this time under ZJP with the 3kg claim coming in handy. He'll take catching. MANDIBLE MAGIC (6) is better than she showed last time out and can return to form with the help of an inside barrier. BLUE MOZART (4) is next best first-up into the preparation.",
